author: nicolemoschella
title: The ladies of “Saturday Night Live” sang their hearts out in this epic goodbye to President Obama
text:
January 22, 2017 5:04 pm The ladies of “Saturday Night Live” sang their hearts out in this epic goodbye to President Obama   
Cecily Strong and Sasheer Zamata are going to miss President Barack Obama. 
On last night’s episode of “Saturday Night Live,” the two funny ladies took to the stage with the heartfelt song, “To Sir With Love,” to say goodbye to the outgoing President. 
“And, as you leave, I know I am losing my best friend,” they sang in unison as a diplomatic photo of Obama appeared on the corner of the screen. 
In the end, they gifted the former president with a mug and Strong made one more plea. 
“Don’t go!” she begged.
